{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ghost|type2=Grass}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ghost|prevnum=710|prev=Pumpkaboo|nextnum=712|next=Bergmite|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Gourgeist}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Gourgeist\n|jname=パンプジン\n|tmname=Pumpjin\n|jtranslit=Panpujin\n|image=711Gourgeist.png\n|category=Pumpkin\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Ghost\n|type2=Grass\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Pickup\n|ability2=Frisk\n|abilityd=Insomnia\n|ndex=711\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=064\n|form1=Small Size\n|form2=Average Size\n|form3=Large Size\n|form4=Super Size\n|height-ftin=2\'04"\n|height-ftin2=2\'11"\n|height-ftin3=3\'07"\n|height-ftin4=5\'07"\n|height-m=0.7\n|height-m2=0.9\n|height-m3=1.1\n|height-m4=1.7\n|weight-lbs=20.9\n|weight-lbs2=27.6\n|weight-lbs3=30.9\n|weight-lbs4=86.0\n|weight-kg=9.5\n|weight-kg2=12.5\n|weight-kg3=14.0\n|weight-kg4=39.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Amorphous\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|expyield=173\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=Brown\n|catchrate=60\n|body=05\n|pokefordex=gourgeist\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Gourgeist\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'パンプジン\'\'\' \'\'Pumpjin\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Ghost|Grass}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Pumpkaboo}} when [[trade]]d.\n\nGourgeist comes in [[List of Pokémon with form differences#Pumpkaboo and Gourgeist|four different variations]]: \'\'\'Small Size\'\'\', \'\'\'Average Size\'\'\', \'\'\'Large Size\'\'\', and \'\'\'Super Size\'\'\'.\n\n==Biology==\nGourgeist is a ghostly Pokémon that has four sizes: Small, Average, Large, and Super Size. Its body is a dark brown pumpkin with a glowing, yellow-orange face carved into the front and a pair of nubby legs. The face consists of two triangular eyes and a grinning mouth; on top of the mouth is a small, triangular cutout for a nose. Poking out of the top of the pumpkin is its slender brown-orange head, which has bright yellow eyes and a small mouth but no visible nose. Gourgeist has long, light pink hair with arm-like tendrils framing its face and bangs that usually cover one eye. On top of its head is a crescent-shaped tuft that is brown on top; this tuft resembles a pumpkin\'s stem.\n\nOn the night of a new moon, Gourgeist wanders town streets while singing an eerie song. Those who hear its song are cursed. It is also known to sing joyfully while observing prey is has entangled in its arms. Gourgeist and its pre-evolution, {{p|Pumpkaboo}}, are the [[Signature move|only known Pokémon]] that can learn {{m|Trick-or-Treat}}.\n\n==In the anime==\n===Major appearances===\n[[File:Jessie Gourgeist.png||thumb|left|250px|Gourgeist in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n====[[Jessie\'s Gourgeist]]====\n[[Jessie]]\'s Pumpkaboo evolved into a Gourgeist in \'\'[[XY082|A Festival Trade! A Festival Farewell?]]\'\'. When Jessie headed to [[Alola]] in \'\'[[SM003|Loading the Dex!]]\'\', it was revealed that Gourgeist had been left behind at {{an|Team Rocket HQ}}.\n\n====Other====\nThree Gourgeist appeared in \'\'[[XY082|A Festival Trade! A Festival Farewell?]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Count Pumpka\'s steward]]. They were commonly used by their {{pkmn|Trainer}} to carry out [[Count Pumpka]]\'s bidding. All three were eventually defeated by [[Ash\'s Pikachu]], [[Clemont\'s Bunnelby]], and [[Serena\'s Braixen]].\n\n===Minor appearances===\nFive Gourgeist appeared in \'\'[[SM094|A Haunted House for Everyone!]]\'\' as illusions created by a {{p|Mismagius}}.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY082|Gourgeist|Ash\'s Pokédex|Gourgeist, the Pumpkin Pokémon, and the evolved form of Pumpkaboo. Gourgeist wander through town at the new moon, surrounding their prey with their arms which resemble hair.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'XY\'\'|Kalos}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Cassius Gourgeist Adventures.png|thumb|150px|Gourgeist in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA Gourgeist appeared in \'\'[[PAXY14|Morphing Manectric]]\'\' under the ownership of [[Cassius]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Gourgeist (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=ghost|type2=grass}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=064|label1=Mountain|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=It enwraps its prey in its hairlike arms. It sings joyfully as it observes the suffering of its prey.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n[[Category:Pokémon in the Galar Pokédex]]<!--\n{{Dex/Gen/1|gen=VIII|reg1=Galar|num1=???}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Sword|v2=Shield|entry=TBD}}\n|}\n|}-->\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=ghost|type2=grass}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=X|v2=Y|t=FFF|area=[[Evolution|Evolve]] {{p|Pumpkaboo}}}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None|v=Omega Ruby|v2=Alpha Sapphire}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VII}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None|v=Sun|v2=Moon|area=[[Pokémon Bank]]}}\n{{Availability/Entry2/None|v=Ultra Sun|v2=Ultra Moon|area=[[Pokémon Bank]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Availability/Footer}}\n\n====In side games====\n{{Availability/Header|type=Ghost|type2=Grass}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=VI}}\n{{Availability/Entry1|1|v=Battle Trozei|color={{defense color}}|area=[[Mountain of Order#Stage 2|Mountain of Order: Stage 2]]}}\n{{Availability/Entry